File: Former president Jacob Zuma's son, Duduzane, wants his father's trial to come to a conclusion PIETERMARITZBURG - Duduzane Zuma says his father's corruption trial needs to come to a conclusion. He was speaking to reporters outside the High Court in Pietermaritzburg. The trial of former president Jacob Zuma has been postponed to the 26th of May. READ: WATCH: Zuma corruption trial postponed He is expected to enter his formal plea then. Zuma is charged with corruption, racketeering, money laundering and fraud, all allegedly in the arms deal of the 1990s. #ZumaTrial: Former president Jacob Zuma’s son Duduzane addresses the media following the postponement of the trial to 26 May 2021. #eNCA #DStv403 pic.twitter.com/o4rCpQhQiK